How to setup a Linux VM on Digital Ocean for BASE token mining
1) Log into Digital Ocean
3) Click Create 4) Click Droplet
5) Pick Region
6) Pick Ubuntu
7) Basic Plan
8) Click to
make blue
9) Use password option
10) Type in “miner” 11) Click to Create
12) Wait until done building
Example of what it looks like when it’s complete building
13) Click on Networking 14) Click on Firewalls 15) Click on Create
16) Enter a name
17) Build these
two rules
18) Click save
19) Enter “miner”
as a tag 20) Click Create
21) Go back to home screen and click on your Droplet (VM).
Yours will have a different name than mine.
22) Click On “Access”
23) Click On “Launch”
24) New Browser
window will open
Congrats… You now have a linux server running in the cloud!
25) Now follow the regular setup guide using the Linux instructions
